{"article_id":"PqXT9eSpcJk57wFi","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"James Comey will deliver bombshell testimony before the Senate Intelligence Committee on Thursday morning ,","depth":7},{"id":1,"text":"that much is clear .","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"He will present a disturbing and detailed account of his interactions with Donald Trump .","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"\" I need loyalty ,","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"I expect loyalty , \"","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"Trump allegedly said to Comey ,","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"according to the former FBI director ' s prepared remarks","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"released on Wednesday .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"Trump ' s firing of Comey in May was suspicious for several reasons .","depth":5},{"id":9,"text":"Most obviously , it occurred against the backdrop of a looming federal investigation into the ties between Russia and Trump ' s campaign ,","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"and","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"even though Trump said at the time","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"that he fired Comey over his handling of the investigation into Hillary Clinton ' s emails ,","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"basically no one believes this ,","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"particularly because Trump himself undermined this argument days later in an interview with NBC ' s Lester Holt .","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"Comey ' s testimony is telling","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"- not only did Trump demand \" loyalty \" and \" honest loyalty \" from Comey ,","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"but he also asked what the FBI director could do","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"to \" lift the cloud \" of the investigation .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"But do Trump ' s actions amount to obstruction of justice ?","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"And what does obstruction of justice mean in this context ?","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"I asked six constitutional and criminal law experts to think through these questions .","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"\" The [ Michael ] Flynn matter surely confirms","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"that he wanted the investigation closed , \"","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"Joshua Dressler , a law professor at Ohio State University , told me","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"after reading Comey ' s prepared remarks .","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"\" But it remains ambiguous whether Trump ' endeavored ' to impede the investigation , \"","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"which is necessary","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"in order to meet the obstruction of justice threshold .","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"For Jimmy Gurulé , a law professor at the University of Notre Dame , Comey ' s statements are more damning :","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"\" It is difficult to construe President Trump 's statements on February 14 to former FBI Director Comey as anything other than a request","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"to terminate the FBI investigation of Gen. Flynn for reasons other than the merits of the case .","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"This is an attempt","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"to endeavor and influence the due administration of justice under the federal obstruction of justice statute . \"","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"Comey ' s testimony will doubtless be just the beginning of discussions","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"over whether Trump committed the crime","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"that forced President Richard Nixon to resign .","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"Obstructing justice seems straightforward :","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"an attempt","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"to impede or undermine a criminal investigation .","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"But there are some important caveats .","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"\" It requires proof","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"that the person corruptly or by threat influences , impedes , or endeavors to influence or impede the due administration of justice , \"","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"Dressler says .","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"\" It does n't require proof","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"that justice was obstructed","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"- only that the person endeavored to influence or impede justice . \"","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"In other words , one needn ' t succeed at obstructing justice","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"to be guilty of it .","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"It ' s enough to prove that someone deliberately sought to hinder an investigation .","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"The problem is that intent is often difficult to prove , especially in a circumstance","depth":6},{"id":51,"text":"where there are multiple contradictory motives .","depth":6},{"id":52,"text":"Mark Tushnet ,","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"who teaches constitutional law at Harvard ,","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"offered an even simpler definition :","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"\" doing something","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"that corruptly interferes with an ongoing investigation ...","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"or doing something","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"that makes it harder for the prosecutor to prove","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"that you committed a crime. \"","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"Corrupt intent means \" specifically wanting to derail an investigation ,","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"to prevent it from reaching what otherwise would be its conclusion . \"","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"It ' s also worth remembering ,","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"according to Brandon Garrett , a law professor at the University of Virginia ,","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"that \" there is a whole family of obstruction of justice statutes ;","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"it 's not just one crime ,","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"and many of them overlap . \"","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"\" In general , \"","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"he continued ,","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"\" obstruction of justice is broadly defined","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"as corruptly influencing or impeding a federal proceedings. \"","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"What actually counts as a \" federal proceeding \" remains a matter of controversy ,","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"and one","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"that bears heavily on this case .","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"We don ' t yet know","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"if there was a grand jury hearing","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"concerning the Russia investigation .","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"If there was ,","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"Trump almost certainly obstructed justice .","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"If , however , there was only a FBI investigation ,","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"Garrett and others","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"I spoke with","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"agree","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"it ' s not clear that obstruction of justice charges are applicable .","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"But setting aside that dispute ,","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"the plainest legal definition of obstruction of justice is something like this :","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"acting with the specific intent","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"to interfere with a judicial proceeding .","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"How strong is the case","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"that Trump obstructed justice","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"based on what we already know ?","depth":6},{"id":91,"text":"There isn ' t an easy answer to this question .","depth":5},{"id":92,"text":"Part of the reason is that we don ' t have all the facts .","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"But it ' s also because of varying views on the powers of the executive .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"Eric Posner , a professor of law at the University of Chicago , pointed out","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"if \" the president is head of law enforcement in this country ,","depth":14},{"id":97,"text":"and if the president is the head of law enforcement ,","depth":14},{"id":98,"text":"then he has the authority","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"to hire and fire","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"and to tell his subordinates not to pursue certain investigations . \"","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"But there are compelling counter-arguments to this :","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"Gurulé ,","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"who also served as assistant attorney general for George H.W . Bush and undersecretary of the Treasury for enforcement under George W. Bush ,","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"insists","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"that the constitutional right","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"to hire and fire","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"is not absolute .","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"\" There ' s no constitutional right","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"to hire and fire","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"that is without exception , \"","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"he told me .","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"Gurulé also sees at least three instances","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"in which the president arguably violated obstruction of justice laws .","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"The first is the actual firing of Comey .","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"\" If it ' s clear that this was done with the aim","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"of interfering with the investigation ,","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"that ' s obstruction of justice . \"","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"The second instance has to do with Trump ' s conversations with Comey .","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"\" We know","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"that the president asked Sessions and others to leave the room","depth":13},{"id":121,"text":"so that he could talk privately with Comey , \"","depth":13},{"id":122,"text":"Gurulé says .","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"\" If the president urged Comey to back off Flynn ,","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"or even if he expressed his desire","depth":14},{"id":125,"text":"to see Flynn left alone ,","depth":14},{"id":126,"text":"that strikes me as endeavoring to influence or obstruct the due administration of justice . \"","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"Still , the question of intent remains .","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"But","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"if it ' s true that this conversation occurred","depth":14},{"id":130,"text":"as reported","depth":15},{"id":131,"text":"and as Comey details ,","depth":15},{"id":132,"text":"it would appear that the president wanted Comey to make a decision regarding the investigation","depth":14},{"id":133,"text":"based on something other than the merits of the case","depth":14},{"id":134,"text":"- and that ' s obstructing justice by any reasonable standard .","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"The third potential instance of obstruction is Trump ' s alleged conversation with Director of National Intelligence Dan Coats .","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"According to the Washington Post ,","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"Trump asked Coats in March","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"\" if he could intervene with then-FBI Director James B. Comey","depth":12},{"id":139,"text":"to get the bureau to back off its focus on former national security adviser Michael Flynn in its Russia probe. \"","depth":12},{"id":140,"text":"As with the Comey interactions , the whiff of obstructionism is strong here .","depth":8},{"id":141,"text":"These are all discrete cases ,","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"Gurulé says ,","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"and they shouldn ' t be conflated .","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"Even if there ' s a sound justification for Comey ' s firing ,","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"\" that doesn ' t pertain at all to the conversation between Trump and Comey or between Trump and Coats . \"","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"Particularly if the prospect of impeachment is in question ,","depth":10},{"id":147,"text":"whether Trump committed obstruction of justice is relevant ,","depth":10},{"id":148,"text":"but that doesn ' t necessarily make it more or less likely to happen .","depth":9},{"id":149,"text":"Ultimately ,","depth":8},{"id":150,"text":"as Christopher Slobogin , a professor of criminal law at Vanderbilt University , told me ,","depth":9},{"id":151,"text":"\" Congress gets to decide what constitutes a high crime and misdemeanor for impeachment purposes . \"","depth":9},{"id":152,"text":"Which is to say ,","depth":8},{"id":153,"text":"even if Trump did obstruct justice ,","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"he will not be impeached","depth":10},{"id":155,"text":"unless a Republican-controlled Congress decides","depth":10},{"id":156,"text":"he ought to be .","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"What legal experts might look for in Comey ' s testimony on Thursday","depth":2},{"id":158,"text":"Some new facts may be revealed","depth":5},{"id":159,"text":"when Comey delivers not only his opening remarks","depth":6},{"id":160,"text":"but also his answers to questions from senators .","depth":6},{"id":161,"text":"Comey will also do a closed-door briefing","depth":5},{"id":162,"text":"following the public testimony .","depth":5},{"id":163,"text":"Legal experts were nearly unified in what they said","depth":5},{"id":164,"text":"they might be looking for .","depth":5},{"id":165,"text":"Eric Posner was focused on \" the reasons for Trump 's firing of Comey and the relative weight","depth":8},{"id":166,"text":"he gave those reasons. \"","depth":8},{"id":167,"text":"If Comey can speak to Trump ' s intent ,","depth":9},{"id":168,"text":"that will go a long way","depth":9},{"id":169,"text":"in determining","depth":9},{"id":170,"text":"whether justice was obstructed .","depth":9},{"id":171,"text":"Again , though , Posner cautioned :","depth":7},{"id":172,"text":"\" We ' ll probably learn","depth":8},{"id":173,"text":"that a whole host of factors drove Trump ' s decision ,","depth":9},{"id":174,"text":"and if so ,","depth":10},{"id":175,"text":"it will be difficult to determine intent . \"","depth":10},{"id":176,"text":"The language","depth":9},{"id":177,"text":"Comey uses","depth":9},{"id":178,"text":"is critical for Christopher Slobogin .","depth":8},{"id":179,"text":"\" If Trump merely said","depth":12},{"id":180,"text":"he ' hoped '","depth":13},{"id":181,"text":"the investigation would end ,","depth":13},{"id":182,"text":"that might not be construed as impeding .","depth":11},{"id":183,"text":"If he said in the context","depth":13},{"id":184,"text":"of talking about the investigation","depth":13},{"id":185,"text":"that Comey should pledge loyalty to Trump ,","depth":12},{"id":186,"text":"that would probably be impeding . \"","depth":11},{"id":187,"text":"It really matters , then , what Trump actually said to Comey .","depth":10},{"id":188,"text":"If Trump insisted","depth":13},{"id":189,"text":"that Flynn was a \" good guy \"","depth":14},{"id":190,"text":"who shouldn ' t be harassed ,","depth":14},{"id":191,"text":"that doesn ' t meet the obstruction threshold . \"","depth":12},{"id":192,"text":"Even if he wanted the investigation shut down or curtailed","depth":15},{"id":193,"text":"because he thought","depth":16},{"id":194,"text":"it was a waste of time ,","depth":16},{"id":195,"text":"\"","depth":14},{"id":196,"text":"Slobogin says ,","depth":13},{"id":197,"text":"\" it might not be improper . \"","depth":12},{"id":198,"text":"Comey has to confirm or at the very least suggest","depth":10},{"id":199,"text":"that Trump wanted to avoid discovery of misdeeds","depth":11},{"id":200,"text":"- by him or by his staff -","depth":11},{"id":201,"text":"in order to have obstructed justice .","depth":9},{"id":202,"text":"Mark Tushnet echoed Slobogin ' s answer .","depth":8},{"id":203,"text":"\" Any indication of reasons","depth":13},{"id":204,"text":"that Trump gave","depth":14},{"id":205,"text":"for asking Comey to go easy on Flynn","depth":14},{"id":206,"text":"will be vitally important , \"","depth":12},{"id":207,"text":"he told me .","depth":11},{"id":208,"text":"\" The specific language is key .","depth":10},{"id":209,"text":"The reporting is that he said","depth":11},{"id":210,"text":"Flynn 's a ' good guy '","depth":11},{"id":211,"text":"but you 'd certainly need more than that","depth":11},{"id":212,"text":"to meet the obstruction of justice threshold . \"","depth":11},{"id":213,"text":"\" I ' m interested in how Comey characterizes the pressure","depth":13},{"id":214,"text":"that was placed on him , \"","depth":13},{"id":215,"text":"Brandon Garrett said .","depth":12},{"id":216,"text":"\" I want to know the intent behind that pressure .","depth":11},{"id":217,"text":"If it 's true that he was pressured to drop the investigation ,","depth":11},{"id":218,"text":"it 's unlikely","depth":12},{"id":219,"text":"that was for arbitrary reasons . \"","depth":12},{"id":220,"text":"Thus ,","depth":10},{"id":221,"text":"if Comey says definitively","depth":12},{"id":222,"text":"that Trump pressured him to drop the investigation ,","depth":12},{"id":223,"text":"Trump will have a hard time","depth":12},{"id":224,"text":"proving","depth":13},{"id":225,"text":"that his intent wasn ' t to \" impede \" or otherwise obstruct the process .","depth":13},{"id":226,"text":"For Joshua Dressler , the bar was comparatively low .","depth":9},{"id":227,"text":"In his view , Comey need only affirm what ' s already been circulated in the media :","depth":10},{"id":228,"text":"\" If Comey merely stands by everything","depth":13},{"id":229,"text":"that 's already been reported in the press","depth":13},{"id":230,"text":"and adds nothing else ,","depth":12},{"id":231,"text":"that alone is enough","depth":12},{"id":232,"text":"to suggest pretty definitively","depth":13},{"id":233,"text":"that justice was obstructed . \"","depth":13}],"relations":[{"parent":467,"left":390,"right":466,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":390,"left":270,"right":389,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":270,"left":248,"right":269,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":248,"left":241,"right":247,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":241,"left":236,"right":240,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":236,"left":235,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":235,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":240,"left":238,"right":239,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":238,"left":237,"right":5,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":237,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":239,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":247,"left":8,"right":246,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":246,"left":9,"right":245,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":245,"left":243,"right":244,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":243,"left":10,"right":242,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":242,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":244,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":269,"left":254,"right":268,"relation":"topic","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":254,"left":251,"right":253,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":251,"left":15,"right":250,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":250,"left":16,"right":249,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":249,"left":17,"right":18,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":253,"left":252,"right":21,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":252,"left":19,"right":20,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":268,"left":260,"right":267,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":260,"left":257,"right":259,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":257,"left":255,"right":256,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":255,"left":22,"right":23,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":256,"left":24,"right":25,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":259,"left":26,"right":258,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":258,"left":27,"right":28,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":267,"left":262,"right":266,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":262,"left":29,"right":261,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":261,"left":30,"right":31,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":266,"left":263,"right":265,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":263,"left":32,"right":33,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":265,"left":34,"right":264,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":264,"left":35,"right":36,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":389,"left":320,"right":388,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":320,"left":284,"right":319,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":284,"left":282,"right":283,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":282,"left":272,"right":281,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":272,"left":37,"right":271,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":271,"left":38,"right":39,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":281,"left":40,"right":280,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":280,"left":277,"right":279,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":277,"left":274,"right":276,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":274,"left":273,"right":43,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":273,"left":41,"right":42,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":276,"left":44,"right":275,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":275,"left":45,"right":46,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":279,"left":278,"right":49,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":278,"left":47,"right":48,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":283,"left":50,"right":51,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":319,"left":293,"right":318,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":293,"left":291,"right":292,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":291,"left":286,"right":290,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":286,"left":285,"right":54,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":285,"left":52,"right":53,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":290,"left":287,"right":289,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":287,"left":55,"right":56,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":289,"left":57,"right":288,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":288,"left":58,"right":59,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":292,"left":60,"right":61,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":318,"left":314,"right":317,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":314,"left":301,"right":313,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":301,"left":297,"right":300,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":297,"left":294,"right":296,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":294,"left":62,"right":63,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":296,"left":64,"right":295,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":295,"left":65,"right":66,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":300,"left":299,"right":70,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":299,"left":298,"right":69,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":298,"left":67,"right":68,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":313,"left":303,"right":312,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":303,"left":71,"right":302,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":302,"left":72,"right":73,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":312,"left":307,"right":311,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":307,"left":305,"right":306,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":305,"left":74,"right":304,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":304,"left":75,"right":76,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":306,"left":77,"right":78,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":311,"left"